gpt_response: To evaluate $\left\lfloor -\frac{5}{3}\right\rfloor$, first we need to see what number $-\frac{5}{3}$ is closest to. Since $-\frac{5}{3}$ is between $-2$ and $-1$, the greatest integer less than $-\frac{5}{3}$ is $-2$. So, $\left\lfloor -\frac{5}{3}\right\rfloor = -2$.
